cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper is about formal verification of smart contracts, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Coq, a proof assistant, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE) in the context of smart contract verification.
